# Design System

## Colors

UNHCR official palette — use the `unhcr.*` Tailwind tokens or the raw hex values below. **Never use Tailwind color names** like `green-500`, `amber-200`, `red-600` etc.

### "Trio" principle — every color family uses exactly 3 steps:
`01 (light bg)` → `Primary accent` → `AAA text`

| Family | Light bg (01) | Primary accent | AAA text |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Blue** (navigation, CTA) | `#CDE3F1` | `#0072BC` | `#05568B` |
| **Green** (header, audio, done) | `#DAF6EB` | `#32C189` | `#1F5741` |
| **Yellow** (tests) | `#FEF1D1` | `#FFC740` | `#684D0B` |
| **Red** (chatbot ring, errors) | `#FCE2DE` | `#D25A45` | `#683229` |
| **Grey** (structure) | `#E5E5E5` | `#737373` | `#262626` |

### Role → hex mapping

| Role | Hex | Token |
|---|---|---|
| Header bg | `#2B9C70` | `unhcr-green-4` |
| Header hover | `#257958` | `unhcr-green-5` |
| Primary CTA (buttons) | `#32C189` | `unhcr-green-3` |
| Primary CTA hover | `#257958` | `unhcr-green-5` |
| Done badge / progress | `#32C189` | `unhcr-green-3` |
| Audio button border+text | `#32C189` / `#1F5741` | `unhcr-green-3` / `unhcr-green-6` |
| Audio button hover bg | `#DAF6EB` | `unhcr-green-1` |
| UNHCR blue (level cards, links) | `#0072BC` | `unhcr-blue-4` |
| UNHCR blue hover | `#05568B` | `unhcr-blue-5` |
| Sidebar active bg | `#CDE3F1` | `unhcr-blue-1` |
| Sidebar active border | `#0072BC` | `unhcr-blue-4` |
| Test card accent | `#FFC740` | `unhcr-yellow-2` |
| Test card text | `#684D0B` | `unhcr-yellow-6` |
| Test card bg | `#FEF1D1` | `unhcr-yellow-1` |
| Chatbot/dictionary ring | `#D25A45` | `unhcr-red-4` |
| Error border | `#D25A45` | `unhcr-red-4` |
| Error bg | `#FCE2DE` | `unhcr-red-1` |
| Error text | `#683229` | `unhcr-red-6` |
| Sidebar bg | `#F5F5F5` | — |
| Body text | `#262626` | `unhcr-grey-6` |

### Rule: namedColors vs large surfaces
- **Primary accent** (e.g. `#32C189`, `#FFC740`, `#D25A45`) — for **small surfaces only**: icons, badges, rings, borders, button text. Max width ≈ button.
- **Light bg (01)** — for hover states, info boxes, card tints.
- **Exceptions** — 2 permitted large surfaces: `#2B9C70` header + `#0072BC` level cards.

Use these exact values — never approximate with Tailwind color names like `green-500`.

## Typography

Font: **Sofia Sans** with Cyrillic subset — already loaded in [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx). No imports needed.
Base size: 16px minimum (prevents iOS zoom on inputs).

## Icons

Use **Lucide React** only. Import named icons directly:
```tsx
import { Menu, X, ChevronDown } from 'lucide-react';
```

## UI Components

Use **shadcn/ui** only — import from `@/components/ui/[name]`:
```tsx
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Card } from '@/components/ui/card';
```

Check `src/components/ui/` for already-installed components before adding new ones.
To install a new shadcn/ui component: `npx shadcn@latest add [name]` (e.g. `npx shadcn@latest add dialog`)

## Common Patterns

**Card/exercise container:**
```tsx
className="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 shadow-md"
```

**Touch targets** — minimum on all interactive elements:
```tsx
className="min-h-[48px]"
```

**Responsive:** mobile-first, single column on small screens. Use `md:` prefix for desktop variants.

**Transitions:**
```tsx
className="transition-colors"   // for hover color changes
className="active:scale-95"     // for button press feedback
```

## RTL Support

Languages `ar` and `fa` are RTL. The `dir` attribute is set on the root element via [src/i18n/LanguageContext.tsx](mdc:src/i18n/LanguageContext.tsx). Use logical CSS properties when needed (`ms-`, `me-` instead of `ml-`, `mr-`).
